HUNGARY NOON RADIO HEADLINES - JULY 3 . These are the main headlines on Hungary ' s Kossuth Radio midday news . Reuters cannot vouch for their accuracy : - - Marta Tocsik , an advisor in the focus of a privatisation scandal over irregular payments , has to pay a tax arrear of 233 million forints . - - The government would like to expand the rights of the Interest Coordination Council , which is made up of the representatives of employers , employees and the government , a senior labour ministry official said . - - The government will discuss today a proposal which would provide agricultural producers with loans totalling 50 billion forints . - - Hungary may have a sugar shortage next year as the sowing area decreased and sugar beat production is not profitable , the National Alliance of Sugar Beat Producers said . - - Budapest newsroom + 36 1 327 4040 
